version_description: Sometimes the app crashed when you tried to invite friends. Rude! That doesn’t happen any more.

What’s on deck? Institutional transfers now consistently do what you’d expect: transfer! For citizens of Norway resident in Canada, we have also verified that Norway is, in fact, a real country. 

New users: heads up! You might get a fresh new experience during signup.

You’re now able to partially transfer your investments – specify exactly how much cash or stock to move to Wealthsimple. Ready to open a new investment account from your phone? You can do that too. Citizens of the U. S. of A., the bug preventing you from signing up has been squashed, welcome aboard! We love getting your reviews and ratings, and take your feedback seriously. Keep it coming!
Get an eagle-eye on everything happening in your portfolio with our all-new Activities view. We love getting your reviews and ratings, and take your feedback seriously – keep it coming!
If you’re transferring an account from a cash-only institution, you can now do a partial – rather than full – transfer! People who just want to dip a toe in, you’re welcome.

We redesigned! Say hello to a more intelligent, more intuitive, more beautiful Wealthsimple. Stay up-to-date with your investments using our new Portfolio page, or deep dive into your individual accounts for a focused look on how things are going. Set up an auto-deposit and see how much more Future You can earn, and then top up your reading list with some expert advice in our new Learn section.

Swipe on those account graphs in a silky-smooth manner, or check your performance in the top-secret landscape mode (by turning your phone). We also tightened the bolts on Activities and Funding, and vanquished a baker’s dozen of small interface hiccups.

Picture this: you’re currently on a bus, train, plane or other method of conveyance, and you've realized you need to add an account to your current portfolio – or transfer an account to Wealthsimple. We’ve all been there. Well, now’s your time to shine! It’s now possible (and encouraged!) to add accounts and set up institutional transfers on your phone. In case you need a hand, we’ve also added live chat to Help and onboarding.

Get onboarded in record time with a shorter, better signup, including the ability to link your bank account using the credentials you already have – no more shaky phone snaps of a void cheque (who uses cheques anymore?) Already invested? Check the new Funding screen to see exactly how quickly your regular contributions stack up.

You're using a long, incomprehensible password, right? Well, we've just made that a whole lot easier by baking in 1Password support. We also took the opportunity to do some cleanup under the hood – nothing you'd notice but we've got this thing purring like a kitten.

Living in the United States? Come on in – we're happy to welcome you into our home. We're serving up a tasty selection of Personal and IRA accounts to get you started. Both Canadian and US users will benefit from updates to make signing up simpler and faster. As always, we love getting your reviews and ratings, and take your feedback seriously – keep it coming!
We didn't paint flames on the side or bolt on a chrome muffler tip, but this release is buzzing like a big block. Lots of small, invisible improvements to our code add up to a smoother, better app.
Signing up as a Wealthsimple client is literally the easiest it's ever been with a baker's dozen of piping hot fixes to our onboarding process, including address autocomplete. Yum!

Imagine: you're in a beautiful bakery. The proprietor hands you an exquisite cupcake and says, "Try this!" Except the bakery is the Wealthsimple app and the cupcake is a brand new, easier way to start investing. You'll also now know if you've reached Wealthsimple Black status, and be able to fund your RESP. Still need to schedule a call with one of our portfolio managers? No problem. In our bakery metaphor you've all just been served a delightful macaron. It is delicious.
Nothing showy, nothing flashy – mostly foundational work for the future. An amuse bouche of a release, not an entrée.

Our clients are nothing if not eagle-eyed, perspicacious arbiters of quality – which is great, they helped us identify a handful of annoying glitches and edge cases which have been banished in this release. Thanks!

We’re making it easier than ever to see how investing can benefit Future You. Our new onboarding gets you saving towards financial goals that you set, and knowing exactly when you’ll reach them. You’ll also get a more tangible breakdown of how your portfolio will be invested. We’d love to know what you think – we read all of your feedback, and ratings are always appreciated.

We’re making it easier than ever to see how investing can benefit Future You. Our new onboarding gets you saving towards financial goals that you set, and knowing exactly when you’ll reach them. You’ll also get a more tangible breakdown of how your portfolio will be invested. We’d love to know what you think – we read all of your feedback, and ratings are always appreciated.

Maybe you moved recently, or use a different name depending on the situation. No sweat – we've improved onboarding to make sure we're catching those personal detail differences earlier and allowing you to verify the correct info. We also made a few adjustments – nothing you'd notice but everything is just a little bit better.

We like to think that Future You made a pretty good choice, investing with Wealthsimple. Nice! Back in the present, we want to reward you for your good choices. We'll apply a credit to your account if you set up a regular contribution, or invite your friends and family to try us out – or just for signing up and funding. It's our thanks for sharing the wealth.

Us, taking the app from the app oven: We've improved the recipe, try this! We addressed a few edge cases, and made it super-easy to invite people who aren't in your address book to try Wealthsimple. We also added a sprinkle of (virtual) cinnamon!

Us, taking the app from the app oven: We've improved the recipe, try this! We addressed a few edge cases, and made it super-easy to invite people who aren't in your address book to try Wealthsimple. We also added a sprinkle of (virtual) cinnamon!

We’ve made it clearer, easier, and just plain nicer to become a client of Wealthsimple – lots of improvements to the signup process based on your feedback. Thanks for helping us craft a better app! Want to share your referral link? No sweat, it's one click away.

A veritable smörgåsbord of improvements and tune-ups to make your investing life better. Share your referral link however you like with native sharing, check your portfolio mix in the app (tap on Holdings!), and get notified if you need to speak to one of our portfolio managers. We also added a sprinkle of appetizing code improvements to support hot new features in the future.

A release chock-a-block full of those good good updates! For a smoother investing experience, we’ll prompt you to set a passcode to get to your deets more quickly, show your account nicknames, and we’ve also fixed a baker's dozen of those things you love to hate: crashes and errors. Keep those reviews coming – we read and appreciate all of your feedback.

Introducing a brand new feature: Roundup. Turn it on, and we'll invest your spare change automatically. It's the best way to put more money to work without really trying.

How does it work? Just link your credit and debit cards to your accounts using our handy-dandy app. We'll round up your purchases, and invest the difference automatically. So your $3.30 cappuccino turns into $0.70 of super-powered future wealth. Magic.
